22 ESTABLISHING OR INCREASING FEES
23 SECTION 5.1.(a) Notwithstanding G.S. 123.1, an agency is not required to consult
24 with the Joint Legislative Commission on Governmental Operations prior to establishing or
25 increasing a fee to the level authorized or anticipated in this act.
26 SECTION 5.1.(b) Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-21.1A(a), an agency may adopt an
27 emergency rule in accordance with G.S. 150B-21.1A to establish or increase a fee as authorized
28 by this act if the adoption of a rule would otherwise be required under Article 2A of Chapter
29 150B of the General Statutes.
