41 elementary school, respectively.
42 (c) Challenges to instructional and supplemental materials shall be made in writing and
43 submitted to the local board of education. The challenge shall specify that the material being
44 challenged is one or more of the following:
45 (1) Obscene.
46 (2) Inappropriate to the age, maturity, or grade level of the students.
47 (3) Not aligned with the standard course of study.
48 (d) The local board of education and the media advisory committee shall only investigate
49 and evaluate challenges submitted by a parent of a student enrolled in a school governed by the
50 board, a teacher employed by the board, or a resident of the area of assignment for the board.
