3 committee. The committee may, in the committee's discretion, request additional information on
4 the subject matter at the hearing from experts employed by the local school administrative unit.
5 Within two weeks of the hearing, the committee shall make a recommendation to the local board
6 of education on whether the challenge has merit and whether the challenged material should be
7 retained or removed as unfit material. The committee's determination shall be limited to
8 considerations of whether the material is unfit on the specific grounds of the material being (i)
9 obscene, (ii) inappropriate to the age, maturity, or grade level of the students, or (iii) not aligned
10 with the standard course of study.
